🧠 Analyst Conclusion

Based on the evidence collected, the domain quora.com and the associated sending IP 18.214.110.142 are confirmed legitimate.

The domain demonstrates:

Long-standing registration history
Proper email authentication configuration
Clean threat intelligence reputation

This case represents a baseline example of a legitimate sender, which is critical for comparison during phishing investigations.

📚 Lessons Learned

This lab reinforced key SOC investigation principles:

Start with headers — they contain the most critical indicators
Correlate multiple data sources — no single tool is sufficient
Understand email authentication — SPF, DKIM, and DMARC are essential
Be tool-agnostic — the same concepts apply across different environments
Establish a baseline — knowing what “normal” looks like improves detection of anomalies
